## ── TASK EXECUTION FLOW ──────────────────────────────────────

### STEP 1 — Decompose
Break every request into atomic subtasks before writing code:
```
TASK PLAN
├── Context : files affected, existing components reused
├── Subtask 1: [Layer] — what, why, which existing pattern applies
├── Subtask 2: [Layer] — what, why, which existing pattern applies
├── Subtask 3: Unit tests for Subtask 1
├── Subtask 4: Integration test for the full flow
├── Subtask 5: Update PROJECT_INDEX.md (if architecture changed)
└── Subtask 6: Update .agent-skills   (if new convention introduced)
```

### STEP 2 — Approval Gate
Stop and wait for explicit approval before proceeding if the plan includes:
  - New service, module, package, or dependency
  - Database schema change
  - Breaking API or contract change
  - Auth / security logic change
  - Removal or replacement of an existing dependency
  - Architectural pattern change
  - Performance-critical algorithm change

  Approval request format:
  ```
  🏗️ APPROVAL REQUIRED
  Change     : [what you want to do]
  Reason     : [why it is necessary]
  Impact     : [files, tests, contracts affected]
  Reuse check: [what existing code was considered first]
  Alternatives: [2 options considered and rejected — with reasons]
  Rollback   : [how to undo if it fails]
  ```

### STEP 3 — Implement
  - One subtask at a time — each must leave the build green
  - Do not refactor unrelated code in the same change
  - Match the code style of the file being edited
  - Use existing utilities/components wherever identified in Step B
  - Prefer composition over inheritance
  - Keep functions under 30 lines; extract if longer
  - No commented-out code in final output

### STEP 4 — Test & Verify  (required for every subtask)
```
VERIFICATION PLAN — Subtask N: [name]
├── Unit
│   ├── Happy path  : [scenario + expected output]
│   ├── Edge cases  : [boundary values, empty inputs, max values]
│   └── Failure path: [error conditions, rejected promises, thrown exceptions]
├── Integration     : [end-to-end scenario through real layers]
├── Snapshot/Visual : [if UI component — include render test]
├── Manual          : [exact steps + expected output]
└── Regression      : confirm full test suite still passes
```

  Test quality rules:
  - Tests are documentation — test names must read as sentences
  - One assertion concept per test (multiple `expect` allowed if they validate one idea)
  - No testing implementation details — test observable behaviour
  - Mock at the boundary (network, DB, file system) — never mock the unit under test
  - Minimum coverage targets: 80% unit, 70% integration (adjust in .agent-skills)

### STEP 5 — Close
  - Update JSDoc/docstrings for all changed public APIs
  - Update `PROJECT_INDEX.md` if architecture changed
  - Update `.agent-skills` if a new convention was introduced
  - Tag introduced tech debt: `// TODO([YYYY-MM-DD]): description`
  - Run lint + type-check + full test suite and confirm green

